1. FreeBSD: Use dagrab to pull audio tracks from a CD. Suggested command line,
   to pull track data from freedb.freedb.org:

      dagrab -d /dev/cdrom -a -v -N -H freedb.freedb.org -P 8880 -C

2. Linux: Use dagrab or grip

3. Ripping to M4a format:

   - Rip CD tracks to .WAV files. (Use grip or dagrab.)

   - Make sure faac is installed and has MP4 support. See
     http://mpeg4ip.sourceforge.net/

   - To convert a WAV file to an M4A file:

	faac -w -q 130 -c 19000 --artist "%a" --album "%d" --year "%y" --title "%n" --track "%t" --genre "%G" -o %m %w

     Escapes are for grip.

4. Playing M4a files on Linux/Unix: Use the following XMMS plugin:

   http://fondriest.frederic.free.fr/realisations/

   The faad2 and faad2-devel RPMs must be installed to build from source.
